computed more efficiently (roughly one-half of the elementary
multiplications can be saved). Also, squaring a \f(CW2\fR\-adic number increases
its precision. For example,
.PP
.Vb 4
\&  ? (1 + O(2^4))^2
\&  %1 = 1 + O(2^5)
\&  ? (1 + O(2^4)) * (1 + O(2^4))
\&  %2 = 1 + O(2^4)
.Ve
