\&\f(CW\*(C`elldata\*(C'\fR database being installed and referencing the curve, and so
is only available for curves over \fBZ\fR of small conductors.
.IX Xref "Mordell-Weil group elldata"
.PP
The library syntax is \fBellgenerators\fR\f(CW\*(C`(E)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "ellgenerators"
.PP
\&\esubsecidx{ellglobalred}\f(CW\*(C`(E)\*(C'\fR: calculates the arithmetic conductor, the global
minimal model of \f(CW\*(C`E\*(C'\fR and the global Tamagawa number \f(CW\*(C`c\*(C'\fR. 
\&\f(CW\*(C`E\*(C'\fR must be an \fIsell\fR as output by \f(CW\*(C`ellinit\*(C'\fR, \fIand is supposed
to have all its coefficients \fR\f(CW\*(C`a_i\*(C'\fR\fI in\fR \fBQ\fR. The result is a 3 component
