\&\f(CW\*(C`r\*(C'\fR of the non-constant polynomial \f(CW\*(C`x = \*(C'\fR\fInf\fR\f(CW\*(C`[1]\*(C'\fR expressed as
polynomials in \f(CW\*(C`r\*(C'\fR. This can be used even if the number field \fInf\fR is
not Galois since some conjugates may lie in the field.
