The library syntax is \fBeigen\fR\f(CW\*(C`(x)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "eigen"
.PP
\&\esubsecidx{matfrobenius}\f(CW\*(C`(M,{\*(C'\fR\fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 0},{v = x})\*(C'\fR: returns the Frobenius form of
the square matrix \f(CW\*(C`M\*(C'\fR. If \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 1\*(C'\fR, returns only the elementary divisors as
a vectr of polynomials in the variable \f(CW\*(C`v\*(C'\fR.  If \fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 2\*(C'\fR, returns a
two-components vector [F,B] where \f(CW\*(C`F\*(C'\fR is the Frobenius form and \f(CW\*(C`B\*(C'\fR is
the basis change so that \f(CW\*(C`M = B^{\-1}FB\*(C'\fR.
.PP
The library syntax is \fBmatfrobenius\fR\f(CW\*(C`(M,\*(C'\fR\fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C`,v)\*(C'\fR, where \f(CW\*(C`v\*(C'\fR is the variable number.
