The library syntax is \fBhnfmod\fR\f(CW\*(C`(x,d)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "hnfmod"
.PP
\&\esubsecidx{mathnfmodid}\f(CW\*(C`(x,d)\*(C'\fR: outputs the (upper triangular)
Hermite normal form of \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR concatenated with \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR times
