to \fBZ\fR\f(CW\*(C`^n\*(C'\fR intersected with the \fBQ\fR\-vector space generated by the
columns of \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR.
.PP
The library syntax is \fBmatrixqz0\fR\f(CW\*(C`(x,p)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "matrixqz0"
.PP
\&\esubsecidx{matsize}\f(CW\*(C`(x)\*(C'\fR: \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR being a vector or matrix, returns a row vector
