.IX Xref "setisset"
.PP
\&\esubsecidx{setminus}\f(CW\*(C`(x,y)\*(C'\fR: difference of the two sets \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR,
i.e.\ set of elements of \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR which do not belong to \f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR.
.PP
The library syntax is \fBsetminus\fR\f(CW\*(C`(x,y)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "setminus"
.PP
\&\esubsecidx{setsearch}\f(CW\*(C`(x,y,{\*(C'\fR\fIflag\fR\f(CW\*(C` = 0})\*(C'\fR: searches if \f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR belongs to the set
\&\f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR. If it does and \fIflag\fR is zero or omitted, returns the index \f(CW\*(C`j\*(C'\fR such that
