integer.
.IX Xref "setsearch"
.PP
\&\esubsecidx{setunion}\f(CW\*(C`(x,y)\*(C'\fR: union of the two sets \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`y\*(C'\fR.
.PP
The library syntax is \fBsetunion\fR\f(CW\*(C`(x,y)\*(C'\fR.
.IX Xref "setunion"
.PP
\&\esubsecidx{trace}\f(CW\*(C`(x)\*(C'\fR: this applies to quite general \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR. If \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR is not a
matrix, it is equal to the sum of \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR and its conjugate, except for polmods
