still runs from \f(CW1\fR to \f(CW\*(C`n\*(C'\fR. In particular, \f(CW\*(C`vector(n,i,expr)\*(C'\fR is not
equivalent to
.PP
.Vb 2
\&      v = vector(n)
\&      for (i = 1, n, v[i] = expr)
.Ve
.PP
as the following example shows:
.PP
.Vb 3
\&      n = 3
\&      v = vector(n); vector(n, i, i++)            \-\-\-\-> [2, 3, 4]
\&      v = vector(n); for (i = 1, n, v[i] = i++)   \-\-\-\-> [2, 0, 4]
