\&\f(CW\*(C`sumnuminit\*(C'\fR. If \fIflag\fR is nonzero, assumes that the function \f(CW\*(C`f\*(C'\fR to be
summed is of real type, i.e. satisfies \f(CW\*(C`\eoverline{f(z)} = f(\eoverline{z})\*(C'\fR, and
then twice faster when \fItab\fR is precomputed.
.PP
.Vb 10
\&  ? a \- b
\&  time = 0 ms.
\&  %1 = \-1.66... E\-308 \e\e abcissa F<sigma> = 2, alternating sums.
\&  ? a \- b
